headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; The Celt and the Saxon. City Missions. New City Hall-The Plans. Commissioners of Emigration. A Drunken Fight--Coroner's Inquest. War on Policy Dealers. New-York Nuisances. Embezzlement--A Store Full of Stolen Goods. Bold Robbery of Shoes. Original Correspondence.

docs.lead_paragraph: Full confirmation of the death of the Czar NICHOLAS has been received by the Atlantic. The details of, his illness are given, nor is there any strong reason for suspecting that he has been removed unfairly. The principal ground for that suspicion was presented in the fact that some former Sovereigns of Russia had unfairly met their death.
